The pressure in all 4 tires must be
checked and set correctly
in order for the
Tire Pressure Monitoring System (TPMS)
to function correctly. Depending on
vehicle type, the tire pressures are found 
on the sticker located either on the
inside of the fuel tank door or in the
driver door frame. For additional
information on tire pressure and the
Tire Pressure Monitoring System (TPMS),
refer to your Owner's Manual.
Once you have checked the pressure
in all 4 tires and adjusted them,
if necessary, press "SET" in the
"Tire Pressure Monitoring System" 
screen.The vehicle will then
 start the programming process.
